(Putting on my MBA hat)
The sample set is constrained to solvers who are serious enough about their stats to self-report them, as opposed to the general solving community. The only meaningful stats are the faster than/slower than average ones. This reliance on self-reporting is also why the Bureau of Labor Statistics is always so terribly wrong about employment numbers.

